text: Kazerun County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Kazerun.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 258,097, in 58,036 families. The county is subdivided into six districts: the Central District, Jereh and Baladeh District, Khesht District, Kamaraj and Konartakhteh District, Kuhmareh District, and Chenar Shahijan District. The county has six cities: Kazerun, Baladeh, Khesht, Konartakhteh, Nowdan, and Qaemiyeh. == References == Category:Kazerun County
